cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automata models and formal languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the properties and restrictions of different types of linear automata. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper introduces a hierarchy of formal languages. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper discusses the acceptance power of different types of linear automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) may also be relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of different classes of linear languages.
